x4freetext: The beam current was integrated using a `split`
Faraday cup divided into four sectors.
Target was a rolled nickd foil, with an isotopic
purity of 99.96% 68Ni. The target thickness of
1.08 mg/cm2 contributed at most 350 keV to the energy
single detector at 159.degr. provided a control
meusurement of accumulated charge times target
The error bars contain the statistical error
only, and they are not shown if smaller than 10%.
